-- CDP sells 1.9 pct Generali stake for 467.5 mln euros
-- By Stephen Jewkes
-- Tue Jul 08, 2014 03:03AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, July 8 (Reuters) - Italy's state-lender Cassa Depositi e Prestiti (CDP) said on Tuesday it had completed the placement of a 1.913 percent stake in insurer Assicurazioni Generali <GASI.MI> at a price of 15.7 euros per share.

In a statement CDP and Fondo Strategico Italiano (FSI), controlled by CDP, said it had raised 467.5 million euros ($637.69 million)from the sale. FSI sold the stake via an accelerated book building process reserved for institutional investors. The sole bookrunner was Merrill Lynch International.